    <bioghist id="aspace_5c793f7e75d5fa789a85438143e6d265">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Robert Summers (1922-2012) was an American economist. He received a B.A. from the
        University of Chicago and he completed his Ph.D. in economics at Stanford University.
        Summers taught at Yale Univesity from 1952-1959 and the University of Pennsylvania
        thereafter until his retirement in 1991. Summers is noted for his research on international
        price comparisons and contributions to the Penn World Tables and International Comparison
        Program, one result of which was the development of purchasing power parity (PPP).</p>
    </bioghist>
